This paper discusses the challenge of explainability in machine learning, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on the need for personalized explanations, which is relevant to the sub-fields of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the use of information theory to formalize explainable ML is also relevant to the sub-field of information retrieval (cs.IR).
